curam.util.persistence.helper

Class ReadOnlyEntityImpl<I,D extends DeepCloneable>

  • java.lang.Object
    • curam.util.persistence.helper.ReadOnlyEntityImpl<I,D>
  • Type Parameters:
    D - the generated Curam "dtls" struct which holds a row of data from the physical database table.
    I - TODO: JavaDoc
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Entity<I>, EntityInfoSetter<I,ReadOnlyEntityImpl<I,D>,D>

    public abstract class ReadOnlyEntityImpl<I,D extends DeepCloneable>
extends java.lang.Object
implements EntityInfoSetter<I,ReadOnlyEntityImpl<I,D>,D>, Entity<I>
    Standard implementation to read a database table. Accesses to data should use ReadOnlyEntityImpl.getDtls(), which forces a read each time; this ensures that the most up-to-date data is used (in the case where code outside of the entity's control may have updated the row's data during the transaction). Note that the forced read may make use of the SDEJ cache facility, and so may not result in an actual database read.
